paragraph.content:
must, as soon as practicable, publish the direction in at least one English
                    and one Chinese language newspaper circulating generally in Hong Kong;
                    and

has obtained registration by fraud or
                    misrepresentation;
                    or (Amended 18 of 2024 s. 17)

guilty of misconduct or neglect in any professional
                    respect;
                    or

the complaint, or a complaint of a substantially similar nature, has
                    previously been inquired into by a disciplinary committee and the Board decided
                    that the disciplinary offence complained of was not committed;

subparagraph.content:
a written notice of the Board’s intention to give a direction under
                            section 24A(1) has been served under section
                            24B(1);

paragraph.content:
a decision made under section 19(1), 20(4) or
                        27(8);
                        (Amended 18 of 2024 s. 22)

an application for the renewal of the registration of a registered
                        social worker received later than 28 days prior to the expiry of the current
                        registration;

the extension or further extension of the period specified in
                            section 34(5) in the case of social work service referred to
                        in section 34(4)(a) or (b) provided by a person;

the person who held the office of the Deputy Chairperson of the Board
                        immediately before the material date ceases to hold that office;
                        and

